claim.claim-text:
1. A method of displaying an image, comprising:
receiving an input image;
receiving a power decrease ratio from a user;
calculating a brightness of an output image corresponding to the input image, which can offset a luminance decrease ratio decreased depending on the power decrease ratio;
controlling the size of each component of a pixel constituting the input image in accordance with the calculated brightness of the output image; and
displaying the output image of the pixel whose component size has been controlled, based on a light source driven by a power decreased by the power decrease ratio,
wherein the calculating the brightness includes:
obtaining a difference between a luminance value corresponding an initial power and a luminance value corresponding to the power decreased from the initial power by the power decrease ratio; and
calculating a brightness of the output image to make the difference equal to a difference between a luminance value corresponding to the brightness of the input image and a luminance value corresponding to the brightness of the output image.

6. A method of displaying an image, comprising:
receiving an input image;
receiving a power decrease ratio from a user;
calculating a brightness of an output image corresponding to the input image, which can offset a luminance decrease ratio decreased depending on the power decrease ratio;
controlling the size of each component of a pixel constituting the input image in accordance with the brightness of the output image; and
displaying the output image of the pixel whose component size has been controlled, based on a light source driven by a power decreased by the power decrease ratio,
wherein the controlling the size of each component includes:
determining a gain K from the brightness of the output image; and
controlling the size of each component in accordance with the determined gain,
wherein the determining the gain includes:
subtracting the brightness of the input image from the brightness of the output image;
obtaining an average for the input image after substituting a brightness of each pixel constituting the input image for a brightness controlling function; and
dividing the subtracted result by the obtained average.

7. An image display device comprising:
an image input device to receive an input image;
a power controller device to receive a power decrease ratio from a user and calculate a brightness of an output image corresponding to the input image, which can offset a luminance decrease ratio decreased depending on the power decrease ratio;
a pixel controller device to control the size of each component of a pixel constituting the input image in accordance with the calculated brightness of the output image;
a light source device driven by a power decreased by the power decrease ratio; and
an image output device to display the output image of the pixel whose component size has been controlled, based on a light source from the light source unit,
wherein the power controller device obtains a difference between a luminance value corresponding to an initial power and a luminance value corresponding to the power decreased from the initial power by the power decrease ratio, and calculates the brightness of the output image to make the difference equal to a difference between a luminance value corresponding to the brightness of the input image and a luminance value corresponding to the brightness of the output image.

8. An image display device comprising:
an image input unit to receive an input image;
a power controller to receive a power decrease ratio from a user and calculate a brightness of an output image corresponding to the input image, which can offset a luminance decrease ratio decreased depending on the power decrease ratio;
a pixel controller to control the size of each component of a pixel constituting the input image in accordance with the calculated brightness of the output image;
a light source unit driven by a power decreased by the power decrease ratio; and
an image output unit to display the output image of the pixel whose component size has been controlled, based on a light source from the light source unit,
wherein the pixel controller determines a gain K from the brightness of the output image, and controls the size of each component in accordance with the determined gain, and
wherein the pixel controller determines the gain by subtracting the brightness of the input image from the brightness of the output image, obtaining an average for the input image after substituting a brightness of each pixel constituting the input image for a brightness controlling function, and dividing the subtracted result by the obtained average.
